ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Timepoint/visit label
Notes: e.g., Baseline, 6-Month Follow Up, Year 2; Morning, At Bedtime

ElementDescription: Time for sample # 1
Time for sample # 2
Time for sample # 3
Time for sample # 4
Time Eat or Drink before Sample # 2
Time Eat or Drink before Sample # 3
What time did you try to go to sleep last night (lights out)?
What time did you wake up today?
How would you rate the quality of your sleep last night?
Notes: 1 = Very bad; 2 = Fairly bad; 3 = Fairly good; 4 = Very good

ElementDescription: Please indicate by marking an X on the line below to what extent you are looking forward to versus dreading today's events.
Notes: 1 = Really dreading today's events; 50 = Neutral; 100 = Really looking forward to today's events

ElementDescription: Please indicate by marking an X on the line below to hat extent you are worrying about how things are going to go today.
Notes: 1 = At ease; 50 = Neutral; 100 = Worrying a lot

ElementDescription: Please indicate by marking an X on the line below to what extent you feel the events of your upcoming day re predictable (you know exactly what's going to happen today).
Notes: 1 = Completely predictable; 100 = Completely unpredictable
